Note.Content: MT HOTTP-C NIV NJPS NJB CEV | RSV NRSV REB GNT "after" = {L:אַחַר<SDBH:אַחַר>}
RSV NIV NJPS NJB NRSV REB GNT CEV | MT HOTTP-B | "that" = {L:אְַשֶׁר<SDBH:אֲשֶׁר>}

It seems that part of the original text is missing | most translations supply the missing part, e.g. RSV "for the people went to the one at Bethel and to the other as far as Dan" | NJPS "for the people went to worship [the calf at Bethel and] the one at Dan"

LEXSense.DefinitionShort: = state in which a countable entity is one in number
= state in which a countable entity is one in number, but implying that there is more than one entity present and that what applies to one entity applies to the other entities as well
plural only: = state in which countable entities are limited in number
= state in which a countable entity is the first in a range
